Chelsea have released their squad that will tackle Wolves in today’s Premier League clash at Molineux Stadium. The Blues manager, Frank Lampard has already confirmed that Antonio Rudiger, Mateo Kovacic and Pedro are fit to play against Wolves, while N’Golo Kante remains sidelined. Chelsea head to the game following a 2-2 draw against Sheffield United in their last Premier League encounter. Below is Chelsea’s provisional squad against Wolves: Arrizabalaga, Azpilicueta, Christensen, Zouma, Rudiger Emerson, Jorginho, Mount, Giroud, Pedro, Pulisic, Caballero, Alonso, Tomori, Barkley, Kovacic, Willian, Abraham, Batshuayi. The kick-off time for the match is 3pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.